def longest_common_subsequence(s1, s2):
    n1, n2 = len(s1), len(s2)
    dp = [[0] * (n2 + 1) for _ in range(n1 + 1)]

    for i in range(n1 + 1):
        for j in range(n2 + 1):
            if s1[i] == s2[j]:
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1
            else:
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1])

    return dp[n1][n2]

This function uses a 2D dynamic programming array dp to store the length of the longest common subsequence between the two input strings, row by row and column by column. The function iterates over the characters of both strings, comparing them pairwise and updating the dp array accordingly. Finally, the function returns the length of the longest common subsequence.

